# Build context for repository/Dockerfile (the `mfb-repo` server image).
#
# The context is the repository root because `repository/` is a workspace member
# and builds against the root Cargo.lock (bug-347). Everything the image needs is
# Cargo.toml, Cargo.lock, and repository/src; the rest of the tree is excluded so
# a multi-gigabyte context does not cross the wire on every deploy.
#
# repository/.dockerignore no longer applies — docker reads only the
# .dockerignore at the root of the build context.

# Build output. `**/` matters: repository/target alone is several GB, and a
# root-anchored `target/` would not match it.
**/target/

# The compiler crate's source. The image builds only `mfb_repository`; the
# Dockerfile writes a stub src/main.rs to satisfy workspace resolution.
/src/
/build.rs

# Test corpus and goldens: the bulk of the tree, none of it in the image.
tests/
benchmark/
examples/
bindings/
third_party/

# Docs and process files.
bugs/
planning/
.ai/
tools/
scripts/

# Databases and local blob data must never enter the builder.
**/*.db
**/*.db-wal
**/*.db-shm
data/
.git/
